<h2 id="traits">Traits</h2>
<p>When hiring a worker at a hut, the primary trait used in that work will be highlighted in <strong>green</strong> and the secondary trait in <strong>yellow</strong> to help you decide which citizen is the best worker for the job. The higher a workerâ€™s level, the faster and more efficient they will be.</p>

<p><img src="../../assets/images/misc/traits.png" alt="Traits" /></p>

<p>These skills make up the workerâ€™s level. The formula is (Primary Trait + Secondary Trait)/4 = Level (rounded down).</p>

<p>For example, if Adaptability is the primary trait and Athletics secondary, and the worker assigned has Adaptability 29 and Athletics 16, then (29+16)/4=11.25.That means that this workerâ€™s level will be 11!</p>

<p>Workersâ€™ skills/levels increase as they work. Their level is limited by the level of the workerâ€™s home. The level of a workerâ€™s work hut and their Intelligence skill level affect the speed that they level up.</p>

